@275 = ~Fireflies Plague~
@276 = ~Fireflies Plague (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 7
Sphere: elemental (fire)
Range: visual range of the caster
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: enemies within visual range
Saving Throw: special

When this spell is cast by the preacher of flames, a horde of fireflies gather and swarm. This swarm will jump first to the target, then to the nearest allies of the target, until six creatures have been affected. Spellcasting within the swarm is impossible (100% failure rate). Creatures in the fireflies plague, regardless of Armor Class, sustain 1D6 point of damage for round, due to the bites and stings of the insects, each one inflicting 1 point of fire damage. Invisibility is no protection. Moreover, if they fail a saving throw each round they can flare up and suffer 1D6 additional point of damage.
Due to the suffocating nature of the swarm, each victim must make a saving vs. spells or run away in fear.~

@277 = ~Incineration~
@278 = ~Incineration (Evocation, Necromancy)
Level: 7
Sphere: necromancy, elemental (fire)
Range: visual range of the caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: 1/2

This spell wraps the target in a vertical column of fire. While burning fire devours it, the victim suffers 2D6 points of damage per round, halved in case of a successful saving throw vs. spells.
A successful dispelling allows to put to an end the burning fire, otherwise it continues to tirelessly burn the target throught the duration of the spell. The fire supplied by the energy of the spell is difficult to extinguish: a shower or a squall are not enough to bring it down. Immersion in a place of water can achieve it, if the water volume is at least equal to that of a lake.
Incineration has no effect on creatures of fire type.~
