@2712 = ~Conjure Fire pseudo-Elemental (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 7
Sphere: summoning, elemental (fire)
Range: visual range of the caster
Duration: 1 turn/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: special
Saving Throw: none

This spell open a portal on the layer of Phlegethos of Baator in order to summon a fire pseudo-elemental subject to the will of the spellcaster. There is a 60% chance that a 12HD pseudo-Elemental appears, 35% of a 16HD pseudo-Elemental answers the call, and a 5% of a 24HD pseudo-Elemental comes to do the housework. It is not necessary to know the language of the summoned creature because the control of the pseudo-elemental is made only by telephatic way. Priests, unlike wizards, do not need to engage a duel of will to take control of the summoned pseudo-elemental. It remains under the control of the caster until the duration of the spell expires.~
